<TITLE> Power companies drive Dhaka stocks </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, April 16 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka stocks rallied to gains Wednesday for a second day, paced by heavy buying into power companies, mutual funds and state-run oil entities. "We have dealt with buying orders of power and oil companies along with mutual funds while pharmaceuticals and banks witnessed mixed closing," an official of brokerage house IDLC Securities told bdnews24.com. Analysts termed the day's trading positive. DSE chief executive Salahuddin Ahmed said that the market was behaving quite normally with more or less balanced buying and selling. "Heavy buying in certain sectors like, power, oil and mutual funds pushed the indices up, but profit taking also occurred in a substantial manner," he told bdnews24.com. The benchmark DGEN or general index maintained an upward trend till the midday sessions and remained more or less stable afterwards. It ended 22.27 points or 0.71 percent higher on 3120.51. The DSI or all share price index finished at 2622.63, rising 18.17 points or 0.69 percent. The bourse's blue-chip DSE-20 also advanced 21.55 points or 0.91 percent to close at 2380.16. Turnover declined to Tk 3.26 billion from Tuesday's Tk 4.12 billion from trading of 31,205,846 shares with gainers beating losers 147 to 100 and seven issues holding steady. AIMS 1st Mutual Fund topped the turnover board, closing at Tk 13.58, up 0.51 percent. Jamuna Oil followed it to end 0.67 percent higher at Tk 282.10. Meghna Petroleum remained steady from previous day's closing to finish at Tk 273.70. Beximco Pharma closed at Tk 88.50, up 3.38 percent. DESCO rose 5.35 percent to Tk 192.50 due to buying pressure. AB Bank also fell 0.64 percent to Tk 3529.50. Square Pharmaceuticals closed at Tk 4595.75, down 1.77 percent. Among the other scrips on the turnover board  Keya Cosmetics, Apex Tannery and AB Bank gained. IFIC Bank and Square Pharmaceuticals ended lower. All the indices on the Chittagong Stock Exchange also ended higher influenced by gains in leather & footwear, engineering and food scrips. The CSCX or selective categories index closed at 5566.82, advancing 34.79 points or 0.62 percent. The CASPI or all-share price index rose 51.31 points or 0.60 percent to end on 8591.13. The CSE-30 blue-chip index ended on 7414.63, up 56.58 points or 0.76 percent. The port city bourse's turnover went down to Tk 468.93 million from Tk 624.57 million the previous day through 5,178,920 shares changing hands. Of the traded issues, 85 advanced, 59 declined and three held steady. bdn
